From: <Richard Stallman>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Subject: Greenwashing disguised as carbon offsets
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Content-Base: https://stallman.org/archives/2024-may-aug.html#12_July_2024_(Greenwashing_disguised_as_carbon_offsets)
Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Greenwashing disguised as carbon offsets</title>
    <base href="https://stallman.org/archives/2024-may-aug.html#12_July_2024_(Greenwashing_disguised_as_carbon_offsets)">
  </head>
  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <p>
The company "Finite Carbon" sells "carbon offsets" based on trees that will be spared the As.
Experts using satellite photos say that
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/article/2024/jul/11/finite-carbon-forest-offsets-analysis">these offsets do little good</a>
for the climate.
<p>
Of course, it is not unusual for businesses to cheat their customers or the public.  Some of
these offsets are fraudulent &mdash; selling a commitment not to cut down trees
<a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2020-sep-dec.html#16_December_2020_(CO2_offsets)">that
won't be cut down anyway</a>.
<p>
Bu what I noticed about these "offsets" is that they can be bogus even by accident.  The trees
in question could be killed, five or ten or twenty years later, by a wildfire, a disease or
parasite, or desertification.

<p>
  </body>
</html>


