From - Wed, 10 Jul 2024 02:49:19 -0000
X-Mozilla-Status: 0041
X-Mozilla-Status2: 00000000
X-Mozilla-Keys:                                                                                 
Received: by localhost; Thu, 18 Jul 2024 07:52:48 -0600
Date: Wed, 10 Jul 2024 02:49:19 -0000
Message-Id: <https://stallman.org/archives/2024-may-aug.html#9_July_2024_(Starmer_Labour_appointing_former_Tory_minister)@localhost.localdomain>
From: <Richard Stallman>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Subject: Starmer Labour appointing former Tory minister
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Content-Base: https://stallman.org/archives/2024-may-aug.html#9_July_2024_(Starmer_Labour_appointing_former_Tory_minister)
Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Starmer Labour appointing former Tory minister</title>
    <base href="https://stallman.org/archives/2024-may-aug.html#9_July_2024_(Starmer_Labour_appointing_former_Tory_minister)">
  </head>
  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <p>
The first thing Starmer Labour will do is <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/article/2024/jul/06/labour-nick-boles-planning-tsar">appoint a former Tory
minister to weaken the planning system requirements</a> for local approval
of construction projects.
<p>
The change might be good or bad -- the article gives few details.
Tories changed these rules to make it particularly easy to block
approval of wind power generators, and reversing that would surely
be a good thing.
<p>
Under the Tory government, <a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2022-nov-feb.html#19_January_2023_(Right-wing_deregulation)">regulations for construction were
circumvented and disobeyed</a>, resulting in building many buildings with
flammable materials.  One of them had a <a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2022-jan-apr.html#14_April_2022_(London_apartment_fire_and_recommendations_for_building_codes)">big fire in which many
residents died</a>.
<p>
Enforcement of safety regulations is not precisely the same issue as
getting approval for a project, but they are related and they are part
of the same system.  A government that is gung ho for "easing
regulations" is likely be insufficiently careful about which ones.

<p>
  </body>
</html>


