dangers, because supposedly it would be cheaper, but it ultimately
cost far more than the estimates.  Much like <a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2022-jul-oct.html#12_September_2022_(High_costs_of_operating_nuclear_power_plants)">a nuclear power plant</a>.
<p>
Ultimately, how did the cost of housing asylum seekers there compare
with the usual cost?  What is the usual cost?

