Date: Tue, 02 Jul 2024 11:56:47 -0000
Message-Id: <https://stallman.org/archives/2024-may-aug.html#30_June_2024_(Oligarchs,_a_history)@localhost.localdomain>
From: <Richard Stallman>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Subject: Oligarchs, a history of injustice
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Content-Base: https://stallman.org/archives/2024-may-aug.html#30_June_2024_(Oligarchs,_a_history)
Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Oligarchs, a history of injustice</title>
    <base href="https://stallman.org/archives/2024-may-aug.html#30_June_2024_(Oligarchs,_a_history)">
  </head>
  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <p>
George Monbiot: *Things are not going to get better as long as
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/article/2024/jun/27/oligarchs-democracies-britain-1945-economic-powers">oligarchs
rule the roost</a> in our democracies.*
<p>
That is true to first order, but not exactly 100% true.  The dominion of the billionaires is
not an all-or-nothing thing, and there are issues important to us which are not particularly
important to them.

<p>
